{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775852887171,"sessionID":"ses_286ec4e68ffeicedQvzP2jwhPv","part":{"id":"prt_d79141529001G14432i1QoQSt2","messageID":"msg_d7913ff80001arVo76OzR5CVLC","sessionID":"ses_286ec4e68ffeicedQvzP2jwhPv","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_87be5b21f30b496bb69c64ef","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-015 — PicoD 命令执行 API Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-015\n- **Module**: `pkg/picod`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Design Stage**: ST-3 completed\n- **Delta Spec**: `changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md` (if exists)\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Project Setup\n\n- [ ] **T001**: Create directory `pkg/picod/`\n- [ ] **T002**: Create `pkg/picod/types.go` with Config, Server, AuthManager, ExecuteRequest, ExecuteResponse, FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, FileEntry, ListFilesResponse structs\n- [ ] **T003**: Create `pkg/picod/constants.go` with TimeoutExitCode (124), MaxBodySize (32<<20), PublicKeyEnvVar, maxFileMode constants\n\n### Phase 2: Authentication Module\n\n- [ ] **T010**: Create `pkg/picod/auth.go` with AuthManager struct and mutex\n- [ ] **T011**: Implement `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` in auth.go - load RSA public key from PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env var\n- [ ] **T012**: Implement `AuthMiddleware()` in auth.go - JWT Bearer token validation with Bearer prefix check\n- [ ] **T013**: Add unit tests for AuthManager - test public key loading failure when env var missing\n- [ ] **T014**: Add unit tests for AuthManager - test invalid PEM format handling\n- [ ] **T015**: Add unit tests for AuthMiddleware - test missing Authorization header returns 401\n- [ ] **T016**: Add unit tests for AuthMiddleware - test invalid Bearer format returns 401\n\n### Phase 3: Workspace & Path Security\n\n- [ ] **T020**: Implement `setWorkspace()` method on Server - validate and set workspace directory\n- [ ] **T021**: Implement `sanitizePath()` method on Server - path traversal prevention using filepath.Clean and symlink resolution\n- [ ] **T022**: Add unit tests for sanitizePath - test path traversal attempt returns error\n- [ ] **T023**: Add unit tests for sanitizePath - test valid path within workspace succeeds\n- [ ] **T024**: Add unit tests for sanitizePath - test symlink traversal prevention\n\n### Phase 4: Command Execution Handler\n\n- [ ] **T030**: Create `pkg/picod/execute.go`\n- [ ] **T031**: Implement `ExecuteHandler` - parse JSON request with Command, Timeout, WorkingDir, Env fields\n- [ ] **T032**: Implement timeout parsing with time.ParseDuration - return 400 for invalid format\n- [ ] **T033**: Implement command execution using exec.CommandContext with context timeout\n- [ ] **T034**: Capture stdout and stderr using bytes.Buffer\n- [ ] **T035**: Return exit code 124 when context deadline exceeded\n- [ ] **T036**: Implement WorkingDir validation using sanitizePath\n- [ ] **T037**: Implement environment variable augmentation (merge with os.Environ)\n- [ ] **T038**: Return ExecuteResponse with stdout, stderr, exit_code, duration, start_time, end_time\n- [ ] **T039**: Add unit tests for ExecuteHandler - test successful command execution\n- [ ] **T040**: Add unit tests for ExecuteHandler - test custom timeout execution\n- [ ] **T041**: Add unit tests for ExecuteHandler - test timeout exceeded returns exit code 124\n- [ ] **T042**: Add unit tests for ExecuteHandler - test invalid timeout format returns 400\n- [ ] **T043**: Add unit tests for ExecuteHandler - test empty command returns 400\n- [ ] **T044**: Add unit tests for ExecuteHandler - test working directory inside workspace validation\n\n### Phase 5: File Handlers\n\n- [ ] **T050**: Create `pkg/picod/files.go`\n- [ ] **T051**: Implement `UploadFileHandler` - detect content type (multipart vs JSON)\n- [ ] **T052**: Implement `handleJSONBase64Upload` - decode Base64 content, validate path, write file\n- [ ] **T053**: Implement `handleMultipartUpload` - parse multipart form, extract path, file, mode\n- [ ] **T054**: Implement `ListFilesHandler` - list files in directory with query param ?path=\n- [ ] **T055**: Implement `DownloadFileHandler` - serve file content at GET /api/files/*path\n- [ ] **T056**: Implement file mode parsing with parseFileMode helper\n- [ ] **T057**: Add unit tests for UploadFileHandler - test JSON Base64 upload success\n- [ ] **T058**: Add unit tests for UploadFileHandler - test multipart file upload success\n- [ ] **T059**: Add unit tests for UploadFileHandler - test invalid Base64 content returns 400\n- [ ] **T060**: Add unit tests for UploadFileHandler - test missing path or file in multipart returns 400\n- [ ] **T061**: Add unit tests for ListFilesHandler - test directory listing successful\n- [ ] **T062**: Add unit tests for ListFilesHandler - test missing path query parameter returns 400\n- [ ] **T063**: Add unit tests for ListFilesHandler - test directory not found returns 404\n- [ ] **T064**: Add unit tests for DownloadFileHandler - test file download successful\n- [ ] **T065**: Add unit tests for DownloadFileHandler - test path escapes workspace returns 403\n- [ ] **T066**: Add unit tests for DownloadFileHandler - test path is a directory returns 400\n- [ ] **T067**: Add unit tests for DownloadFileHandler - test file not found returns 404\n\n### Phase 6: Health Check & Server\n\n- [ ] **T070**: Create `pkg/picod/health.go`\n- [ ] **T071**: Implement `HealthCheckHandler` - return status, service, version, uptime (no auth required)\n- [ ] **T072**: Create `pkg/picod/server.go`\n- [ ] **T073**: Implement `NewServer()` - initialize Gin engine, load auth, setup routes\n- [ ] **T074**: Implement `setupRoutes()` - configure /api/* routes with auth middleware, /health without auth\n- [ ] **T075**: Implement `Run()` method - start HTTP server\n\n### Phase 7: Main Entry Point\n\n- [ ] **T080**: Create `cmd/picod/main.go`\n- [ ] **T081**: Parse CLI flags: -port (default 8080), -workspace (default current dir)\n- [ ] **T082**: Initialize Config and create Server\n- [ ] **T083**: Call server.Run() with proper error handling\n- [ ] **T084**: Add unit tests for CLI defaults\n- [ ] **T085**: Add integration test - server starts on configured port\n\n### Phase 8: Build & Verification\n\n- [ ] **T090**: Run `go build ./cmd/picod` - verify build succeeds\n- [ ] **T091**: Run `go test ./pkg/picod/...` - verify all unit tests pass\n- [ ] **T092**: Run HTTP server and verify it responds on configured port\n- [ ] **T093**: Verify JWT auth is enforced on /api/* endpoints\n- [ ] **T094**: Verify /health endpoint works without authentication\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- gin v1.9.1 (already in go.mod)\n- golang-jwt/jwt/v5 v5.2.1 (already in go.mod)\n- k8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1 (already in go.mod)\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── types.go        # Data structures (Config, Server, AuthManager, requests/responses)\n├── constants.go    # Constants (TimeoutExitCode, MaxBodySize, etc.)\n├── auth.go         # AuthManager, LoadPublicKeyFromEnv, AuthMiddleware\n├── execute.go      # ExecuteHandler\n├── files.go        # UploadFileHandler, ListFilesHandler, DownloadFileHandler\n├── health.go       # HealthCheckHandler\n├── server.go       # NewServer, setupRoutes, Run\n└──\n\ncmd/picod/\n└── main.go         # CLI entry point\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- All handlers must use workspace path validation via sanitizePath before file operations\n- JWT validation must check for \"Bearer \" prefix\n- Timeout exit code must be 124 (consistent with Unix timeout command)\n- All /api/* endpoints require JWT auth; /health does not\n- Request body size limited to 32 MiB via MaxBodySize","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/picod/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775852887158,"end":1775852887168}}}}
